articles.description: Tevon Saddler and Roddy Peters scored 15 points apiece, and Nicholls held on to beat Sam Houston State 73-72 on Wednesday night for its fourth straight win.
articles.headline: Nicholls holds off Sam Houston State 73-72

articles.description: Aaron Cook sank two free throws with four seconds remaining in overtime, Armon Fletcher scored 22 points and Southern Illinois turned back Missouri State 81-80 Wednesday night, running its record to 7-1 over the last eight games.
articles.headline: Cook late FTs lift S. Illinois over Missouri St. 81-80, OT

articles.description: Forward Yante Maten earns his tenth double-double to push the Bulldogs to a dramatic road win over the Gators.
articles.headline: UGA squeaks past Florida in OT 72-69

images.caption: Forward Yante Maten earns his tenth double-double to push the Bulldogs to a dramatic road win over the Gators.
images.name: UGA squeaks past Florida in OT 72-69

articles.description: Jaron Hopkins scored 16 of his 20 points in the second half when Deshon Taylor scored 12 of his 19 and Fresno State pulled away for a 77-57 win over San Jose State on Wednesday night.
articles.headline: Hopkins, Taylor lead Fresno State past San Jose State 77-57

articles.description: Yante Maten scored 23 points, including a huge 3-pointer to send the game into overtime, and Georgia beat Florida 72-69 Wednesday night to end a three-game losing streak in Southeastern Conference play.
articles.headline: Maten scores 23, Georgia sweeps Florida with 72-69 OT win

images.caption: Forward Yante Maten earns his tenth double-double to push the Bulldogs to a dramatic road win over the Gators.
